<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880405-0133 </DOCNO><HL> Foxboro Holder Rights Plan </HL><SO> </SO><CO> FOX </CO><IN> DIV </IN><DATELINE> FOXBORO, Mass.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Foxboro Co. said its board approved a shareholder rights plan under which shareholders will receive a preferred stock purchase right for each common share held.    The rights, payable on April 15 to shareholders of record on the same date, expire on April 14, 1998, and are exercisable only under certain circumstances.    The maker of industrial-control equipment said it is not aware of any attempt to acquire it. </TEXT></DOC>